\f0\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0  Genesis: From Life Detours to Audio Adventures\

\fs20 In the stormy wake of a divorce back in 2021\'962022, I needed something to anchor myself. Something immersive. Something that could pull me so deep into the zone that the noise outside would fade into irrelevance.\
That \'93something\'94 became PlayEm.\
I've always had a habit\'97some might call it a compulsion\'97of building audio players. From the golden days of the Commodore 64 to the Atari ST, and through the decades across Windows, Linux, NeXTSTEP, iOS, and macOS, I\'92ve been coding my own way to listen to music. Because for me, music isn\'92t just background\'97it\'92s atmosphere, mood, escape. It\'92s the heartbeat of my day.\
So it only made sense that I\'92d build a music player just for me. But not just any player\'97an opinionated one. One tailored not to the generic \'93play song, skip song\'94 pattern, but to how I actually consume music: long-form electronic DJ sets, not bite-sized tracks. That one difference alone has guided every feature and design decision in PlayEm.
