\f0\fs20 \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 Let\'92s get real for a second\'97PlayEm isn\'92t perfect. It\'92s a personal proof of concept, not a polished commercial product.\
For starters, it still depends on Music.app for its library. Yes, it can write metadata changes\'85 but don\'92t expect Music.app to play nice and instantly show those edits. Apple didn\'92t design it with third-party players in mind.\
Also: no streaming. Files must be local. No Apple Music, no Spotify, no SoundCloud\'97yet.\
The current architecture expects to fully load and decode a track before doing any of the juicy analysis and visualization. Streaming support would require a full-on re-architecture, and let\'92s just say\'85 not today.\
I\'92ve toyed with adding a local database to make PlayEm more independent, especially since Music.app won\'92t support attributes like musical key. That\'92s likely coming in the future\'97just not this release.\
I also experimented with tempo-shifting while maintaining key using Rubberband, but it didn\'92t quite gel with the existing system\'97especially when dealing with percussive-heavy tracks. That one\'92s on the back burner too.\
Volume adaptation depending on the average volume and / or metadata from the file itself is something I felt a proper player needs to have while PlayEm currently does not. \
